{
  "stem": "22869.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And by about 8 o'clock-- I didn't know at that time what time it was, sounded to me like-- like it's midnight-- around 8 o'clock, I had two flashlights shining in my face, and some guys yelling, get up!",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Get up!",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Get up!",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In Slovakish.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were guys who came to take me away.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And in the commotion, my mother, of course, was-- was crying.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Of course, maybe-- maybe it's better, yet today, that-- that she didn't know what-- where I'm heading.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So the thought was-- and that's what they convinced us, even the Jewish leaders, that it's a question of going away for a couple of months to forced labor.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And personally, I really wasn't afraid of a couple of months of forced labor, because I was a kind of a guy-- I thought, I'll survive a couple of months of forced labor.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It's not the worst thing in the world.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I mean, we had-- we had, before, they used to take Jews already a year, two years before.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We used to have in winter a lot of snow, they would take Jewish people to-- to shovel the snow, for days-- days in, days out.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And nobody gets killed from a little work.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It's not the most pleasant thing that you're being subjugated to and picked just because you're Jewish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But we thought, for survival purposes, we'll do it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they took me away that evening, and the-- the two fellows who woke me up first-- I was the youngest-- took me along the street [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We went from house to house, and they had a list whom to take.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then they deposited us to a gathering place, which was a public school, really.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
